reviewText: what we have here is 3 comedys and for a low price all of them are a laugh a minute.
Who's Your Daddy was fairly good...funny and a decent storyline. Th other films were okay.
The movies were good.  Not academy award winners but entertaining

3 college kid movies that try to be funny, but don't quite make it. Freshman Orientation concerns a kid who can't get the girl, but finally succeeds by pretending to be gay. Foreign Exchange contains foreign stereotypes, the usual one. Who's your daddy is about a kid who suddenly inherits money he wasn't aware of and becomes an a-hole. Predictably he falls on hard times, his friends come to his aid and teach him life lessons. Lots of pretty girls, that's about it.
If your buying it for the nudity, don't bother.
